{!<div style="text-align: center;">!} 
<em>"The events of May have marked a turning point in the political life of the state, leading to a significant increase in the power and authority of the government, while simultaneously weakening the role of the parliament. The unchecked dominance of the legislative Sejm eventually led to its decline, giving rise to the supremacy of the government. The state now fluctuates between these two problematic and harmful extremes. It is high time to restore balance and foster harmonious cooperation between the legislative and executive branches of government!"</em>
<h5><strong>Ignacy Daszyński</strong></h5>
<h7><em>On the First Anniversary of the May Coup, 1927</em></h7>
{!</div>!}


<p style="text-align: justify">This is a game of alternate history. While historical accuracy is a major concern, keep in mind that this is a *game*, and that any divergence from actual events will necessarily have to involve some element of make-believe. Nevertheless, please let the author know if there are any glaring mistakes.

For more information on the politics and government of the Polish Republic, see the “Library” page on the top left. If this is your first time playing the game, it is strongly recommended that you read at least some of this information.</p>

- @1928_main: Begin (normal difficulty)

@1928_main
audio: shuffle music/1928_1930/FruhlingsliedMendelssohn.mp3 music/1928_1930/AUF_HOHEN_BERGEN_noise_reduced.mp3 music/1928_1930/MarekWeber.mp3 music/1928_1930/BAUERNKAPELLE.mp3 music/1928_1933/DERLINDENBAUM_normalized.mp3 music/1928_1933/ZurSonne_zurFreiheit.mp3 music/1928_1933/arbeiter_marseille.mp3 music/1928_1933/Wann_wir_schreiten_Seit_an_Seit.mp3 music/1930_1933/Internationale-de_normalized.ogg
new-page: true
go-to: main if difficulty >= 0; main.main_easy if difficulty < 0

= 1928

<p style="text-align: justify">It is a bright time for Independent Poland. After a period of struggle, inflation is finally under control, and the economy is expanding steadily. We've brought long awaited political stability to public life.

The caretaker government of Józef Piłsudski is preparing for 1928 elections. It will be a major test for our political vision.</p>



